[thinking] **Exploring custom ClassLoader**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m thinking about a custom ClassLoader that returns only a temporary factory file and delegates class loading to its parent. This avoids permanent resources. I noticed that Existing PropertiesLoaderUtilsTest has a null parent for FixedResourcesClassLoader, which isn't ideal for ClassUtils.forName. 
[thinking] 
[thinking] I could extend ClassLoader for a parent test ClassLoader and override getResources to return a temporary URL for the FACTORIES_RESOURCE_LOCATION. That way, it could load factory names correctly. It seems like a decent plan to ensure that the factory loading works smoothly with the required classes!
[thinking] 
